Despite the need for computing professionals and high salaries, the majority of Computer Science (CS) majors at Colorado School of Mines in a pre-service teaching methods class (CS Teaching Techniques) reported interest in becoming K-12 teachers. Get The Facts Out survey results from a customized myth-busting presentation about K-12 teaching careers confirm that, even among students pursuing a teaching minor, K-12 teaching satisfaction, salaries, and pensions are misunderstood in comparison to industry careers. More students may be attracted to CS teaching careers utilizing Get The Facts Out state-by-state presentation materials.